<section xml:id="C10.S35">
<title>Generating Function and Associated Series</title>          
<para xml:id="C10.S35.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C10.S35.p1.s1">
For <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S35.p1.m1">z\in\mathbb{C}</Math> and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S35.p1.m2">t\in\mathbb{C}\setminus\{0\}</Math> , <Math equation-number="10.35.1" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S35.E1">e^{\frac{1}{2}z(t+t^{-1})}=\sum_{m=-\infty}^{\infty}t^{m}I_{m}\left(z\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<para xml:id="C10.S35.p2">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C10.S35.p2.s1">
Jacobiâ€“Anger expansions: for <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C10.S35.p2.m1">z,\theta\in\mathbb{C}</Math> , <Math equation-number="10.35.2" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S35.E2">e^{z\cos\theta}=I_{0}\left(z\right)+2\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}I_{k}\left(z\right) \cos\left(k\theta\right),</Math> <Math equation-number="10.35.3" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S35.E3">e^{z\sin\theta}=I_{0}\left(z\right)+2\sum_{k=0}^{\infty}(-1)^{k}I_{2k+1}\left( z\right)\sin\left((2k+1)\theta\right)+2\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}(-1)^{k}I_{2k}\left( z\right)\cos\left(2k\theta\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C10.S35.p2.s2">
<Math equation-number="10.35.4" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S35.E4">1=I_{0}\left(z\right)-2\!I_{2}\left(z\right)+2\!I_{4}\left(z\right)-2\!I_{6} \left(z\right)+\cdots,</Math> <Math equation-number="10.35.5" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S35.E5">e^{\pm z}=I_{0}\left(z\right)\pm 2\!I_{1}\left(z\right)+2\!I_{2}\left(z\right) \pm 2\!I_{3}\left(z\right)+\cdots,</Math> <Math equation-number="10.35.6" mode="display" xml:id="C10.S35.E6">\cosh z=I_{0}\left(z\right)+2\!I_{2}\left(z\right)+2\!I_{4}\left(z\right)+2\!I _{6}\left(z\right)+\dots,\sinh z=2\!I_{1}\left(z\right)+2\!I_{3}\left(z\right)+2\!I_{5}\left(z\right)+\dots</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</section>
